00:00:02.500 --> 00:00:04.636 position:5% line:89% align:start
[cicadas buzzing]

00:00:05.704 --> 00:00:07.507 position:5% line:89% align:start
[Tomoya] Nice weather, huh?

00:00:07.607 --> 00:00:09.042 position:5% line:89% align:start
[Nagisa] Yeah!

00:00:09.142 --> 00:00:11.010 position:5% line:83% align:start
Seems like a waste
to go to class.

00:00:11.110 --> 00:00:14.048 position:5% line:83% align:start
Why don't we skip and
go to the beach?

00:00:14.148 --> 00:00:16.686 position:5% line:83% align:start
Give it up already, Okazaki.
You say that every day!

00:00:16.786 --> 00:00:20.089 position:5% line:77% align:start
Of course, cause these
supplementary classes
are a waste of time.

00:00:20.189 --> 00:00:22.426 position:5% line:83% align:start
If I'm not going to college,
then there's no point.

00:00:22.526 --> 00:00:25.865 position:5% line:77% align:start
It doesn't matter.
You made a commitment,
so you have to honor it.

00:00:25.965 --> 00:00:28.167 position:5% line:83% align:start
Besides, it still goes
on your school record.

00:00:28.267 --> 00:00:30.670 position:5% line:83% align:start
[sigh] You sure like to worry
about me, don't you?

00:00:30.770 --> 00:00:33.173 position:5% line:89% align:start
Well, what do you expect?

00:00:33.273 --> 00:00:36.110 position:5% line:89% align:start
I mean, because you're, um...

00:00:36.210 --> 00:00:39.682 position:5% line:83% align:start
you're very special to me,
Okazaki.

00:00:39.782 --> 00:00:42.118 position:5% line:89% align:start
[Tomoya] [gulps nervously]

00:00:43.454 --> 00:00:44.355 position:5% line:89% align:start
Hey, Nagisa!

00:00:44.455 --> 00:00:45.623 position:5% line:89% align:start
Uh huh, yeah?!

00:00:45.724 --> 00:00:47.692 position:5% line:89% align:start
You, um, wanna hold hands?

00:00:47.792 --> 00:00:48.928 position:5% line:89% align:start
[Nagisa] Uh! Huh?

00:00:49.027 --> 00:00:50.263 position:5% line:89% align:start
Just try it.

00:00:50.363 --> 00:00:52.900 position:5% line:83% align:start
I-I don't know.
I mean, we're in public.

00:00:53.000 --> 00:00:54.368 position:5% line:89% align:start
What if someone sees us?

00:00:54.468 --> 00:00:56.771 position:5% line:83% align:start
There's nobody around.
Don't worry about it.

00:00:56.871 --> 00:00:57.940 position:5% line:89% align:start
[motorcycle engine]

00:00:58.039 --> 00:00:59.340 position:5% line:83% align:start
Besides, we're going out,
aren't we?

00:00:59.441 --> 00:01:01.011 position:5% line:83% align:start
What's wrong with holding hands
once in a while?

00:01:01.110 --> 00:01:02.344 position:5% line:89% align:start
[motorcycle engine]

00:01:02.444 --> 00:01:05.783 position:5% line:83% align:start
I-I guess you have a point.
No harm in trying.

00:01:08.954 --> 00:01:10.522 position:5% line:83% align:start
Good morning!
[motorcycle engine]

00:01:10.622 --> 00:01:13.393 position:5% line:89% align:start
Coming through!

00:01:13.493 --> 00:01:15.261 position:5% line:83% align:start
Lovey-dovey first thing
in the morning.

00:01:15.361 --> 00:01:18.132 position:5% line:77% align:start
Wait, don't tell me you were
about to kiss before I
interrupted?

00:01:18.232 --> 00:01:20.268 position:5% line:83% align:start
Come on, don't be stupid!
Of course not!

00:01:20.368 --> 00:01:22.538 position:5% line:83% align:start
Yeah, what he said.
We haven't started kissing yet.

00:01:22.638 --> 00:01:24.641 position:5% line:83% align:start
We were just trying to hold-
(umph!)

00:01:24.741 --> 00:01:26.610 position:5% line:89% align:start
[Tomoya] Hey, shut up!

00:01:26.710 --> 00:01:28.713 position:5% line:89% align:start
[giggles]

00:03:02.035 --> 00:03:05.006 position:5% line:77% align:start
[Tomoya]
 <i>The school festival is over,</i>
 <i>we're finished with exams,</i>

00:03:05.106 --> 00:03:07.308 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>and summer vacation</i>
 <i>is finally here.</i>

00:03:07.408 --> 00:03:11.548 position:5% line:77% align:start
 <i>Still, not much has changed and</i>
 <i>I'm still freeloading at</i>
 <i>Nagisa's house.</i>

00:03:11.648 --> 00:03:14.051 position:5% line:83% align:start
Thus, the price of rice rose
steadily, and in Toyama...

00:03:14.151 --> 00:03:15.820 position:5% line:77% align:start
[Tomoya] <i>Even though</i>
 <i>it's summer vacation,</i>
[teacher continues lecturing]

00:03:15.920 --> 00:03:18.857 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>seniors like me still have</i>
 <i>supplementary classes.</i>

00:03:18.957 --> 00:03:21.494 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>But I'm toughing it out for</i>
 <i>Nagisa's sake at least.</i>

00:03:21.594 --> 00:03:24.397 position:5% line:83% align:start
[Teacher] Are there any
questions before I move on?

00:03:29.939 --> 00:03:32.943 position:5% line:83% align:start
[Kyou] Every day, nothing but
study, study, study.

00:03:33.043 --> 00:03:34.211 position:5% line:89% align:start
I'm so sick of all this.

00:03:34.310 --> 00:03:35.812 position:5% line:83% align:start
It's the last summer vacation
of our lives

00:03:35.912 --> 00:03:38.983 position:5% line:83% align:start
and we're stuck indoors
reading books all day.

00:03:39.918 --> 00:03:41.386 position:5% line:89% align:start
You might think it's boring,

00:03:41.487 --> 00:03:43.723 position:5% line:83% align:start
but I'm actually happy to be
studying with everyone for once.

00:03:43.823 --> 00:03:48.362 position:5% line:77% align:start
And on the bright side,
we still get to eat lunch
together every day, right?

00:03:48.462 --> 00:03:49.731 position:5% line:89% align:start
That reminds me...

00:03:49.831 --> 00:03:51.666 position:5% line:83% align:start
What the heck are you doing
lurking around here?

00:03:51.767 --> 00:03:54.504 position:5% line:83% align:start
As Student Council President,
I'm required to come to school.

00:03:54.604 --> 00:03:57.541 position:5% line:77% align:start
I know that! I'm asking
why you're hanging out
with us every day

00:03:57.641 --> 00:03:59.643 position:5% line:83% align:start
when you're not even
in the Drama Club!

00:03:59.744 --> 00:04:02.748 position:5% line:83% align:start
Where's Okazaki?
I haven't seen him.

00:04:02.848 --> 00:04:03.549 position:5% line:89% align:start
(oh?)

00:04:03.649 --> 00:04:04.884 position:5% line:89% align:start
Oh, I forgot to tell you.

00:04:04.984 --> 00:04:07.854 position:5% line:83% align:start
Okazaki said he was going
over to Sunohara's.

00:04:07.954 --> 00:04:08.890 position:5% line:89% align:start
[Tomoyo] (uh...)

00:04:08.990 --> 00:04:10.758 position:5% line:89% align:start
Uh, is something wrong?

00:04:10.858 --> 00:04:13.695 position:5% line:83% align:start
I just noticed that you
still call him Okazaki.

00:04:13.796 --> 00:04:16.166 position:5% line:83% align:start
Yes, is something
wrong with that?

00:04:16.266 --> 00:04:17.700 position:5% line:89% align:start
I wouldn't say it's "wrong",

00:04:17.801 --> 00:04:20.905 position:5% line:83% align:start
but since Tomoya calls you
Nagisa, it does seem a bit odd.

00:04:21.005 --> 00:04:24.243 position:5% line:77% align:start
If you two are going out,
then shouldn't you be
on a first name basis?

00:04:24.342 --> 00:04:29.650 position:5% line:77% align:start
Oh, now that you mention it, I
seem to remember someone telling
me the same thing before.

00:04:29.750 --> 00:04:32.887 position:5% line:83% align:start
So, let's hear it. How far
have you two gone anyway?

00:04:32.987 --> 00:04:34.489 position:5% line:89% align:start
Huh?!

00:04:36.091 --> 00:04:37.827 position:5% line:89% align:start
Well, actually...

00:04:37.928 --> 00:04:40.630 position:5% line:83% align:start
[Youhei] What? You haven't
even held hands yet?!

00:04:40.730 --> 00:04:42.399 position:5% line:89% align:start
What are you, in grade school?

00:04:42.500 --> 00:04:45.304 position:5% line:77% align:start
Next you're gonna tell me
you're afraid she's gonna
give you cooties!

00:04:45.436 --> 00:04:46.772 position:5% line:89% align:start
[Tomoya] Shut up.

00:04:46.872 --> 00:04:49.275 position:5% line:83% align:start
When the moment comes,
it can be really nerve-wracking.

00:04:49.375 --> 00:04:53.681 position:5% line:77% align:start
Ah, I can't believe Nagisa's
wasting her time who
won't even hold her hand.

00:04:53.781 --> 00:04:58.521 position:5% line:77% align:start
She should get with me, so I can
teach her the true meaning of
love. [knock on door]

00:04:58.621 --> 00:05:01.457 position:5% line:83% align:start
Sunohara, you have a visitor.
[Youhei] Huh? Me?

00:05:01.558 --> 00:05:03.895 position:5% line:89% align:start
Yeah, and she's really cute too.

00:05:03.995 --> 00:05:05.463 position:5% line:89% align:start
She can't wait to see you.

00:05:05.563 --> 00:05:07.733 position:5% line:89% align:start
WHAT?! FOR REAL?!

00:05:07.833 --> 00:05:10.270 position:5% line:89% align:start
YAHAA!!!

00:05:10.369 --> 00:05:12.340 position:5% line:89% align:start
(sighs)

00:05:12.439 --> 00:05:14.308 position:5% line:89% align:start
Sorry to keep you waitin', Baby!

00:05:14.407 --> 00:05:15.910 position:5% line:89% align:start
Youhei, hi!

00:05:16.010 --> 00:05:18.680 position:5% line:89% align:start
[Youhei] (urk...)

00:05:20.449 --> 00:05:21.417 position:5% line:89% align:start
Mei, it's you.

00:05:21.517 --> 00:05:23.153 position:5% line:89% align:start
It's been a while, huh, Okazaki?

00:05:23.254 --> 00:05:25.089 position:5% line:89% align:start
Nice to see you!

00:05:26.557 --> 00:05:29.228 position:5% line:83% align:start
I called and told you I was
coming over today, didn't I?

00:05:29.328 --> 00:05:30.997 position:5% line:89% align:start
Why are you surprised?

00:05:31.097 --> 00:05:32.900 position:5% line:89% align:start
[Youhei] Sorry, I forgot.

00:05:33.000 --> 00:05:36.337 position:5% line:83% align:start
Ah, you're hopeless, Youhei.
Give me a break.

00:05:36.436 --> 00:05:37.772 position:5% line:83% align:start
When we're finished
cleaning up in here,

00:05:37.872 --> 00:05:40.441 position:5% line:83% align:start
why don't we go say hi
to Nagisa's mom and dad?

00:05:40.542 --> 00:05:42.711 position:5% line:89% align:start
[Mei] Okay!

00:05:45.582 --> 00:05:47.718 position:5% line:89% align:start
[ALL] Thanks for the food!

00:05:50.856 --> 00:05:53.326 position:5% line:83% align:start
(giggle) You're always so polite
and well-mannered, Mei.

00:05:53.425 --> 00:05:55.095 position:5% line:89% align:start
It's a pleasure to have you.

00:05:55.195 --> 00:05:58.233 position:5% line:77% align:start
When you put it that way,
it's hard to believe she's
Sunohara's sister.

00:05:58.333 --> 00:05:59.701 position:5% line:83% align:start
You shouldn't say
things like that.

00:05:59.801 --> 00:06:02.238 position:5% line:83% align:start
I think Sunohara is a
very nice person.

00:06:02.338 --> 00:06:06.143 position:5% line:77% align:start
Mei, if you're looking for a
place to stay, I hope you
know you're welcome here.

00:06:06.243 --> 00:06:07.844 position:5% line:89% align:start
Oh, really? You don't mind?

00:06:07.945 --> 00:06:09.847 position:5% line:83% align:start
Of course not!
It's our pleasure!

00:06:09.948 --> 00:06:11.784 position:5% line:89% align:start
[all laugh]

00:06:11.884 --> 00:06:14.586 position:5% line:71% align:start
We should all take
a bath after this.
[Tomoya] <i>This family sure loves</i>
 <i>company, don't they?</i>

00:06:14.687 --> 00:06:16.523 position:5% line:89% align:start
[Sanae] Oh, count me in too!

00:06:20.262 --> 00:06:21.696 position:5% line:89% align:start
[Akio] Hmm...

00:06:21.797 --> 00:06:23.231 position:5% line:83% align:start
[Nagisa] It's a bit crowded in
here. I hope you don't mind.

00:06:23.333 --> 00:06:26.035 position:5% line:83% align:start
Seem to be enjoying themselves.
[Mei] No, of course not,

00:06:26.135 --> 00:06:29.473 position:5% line:71% align:start
If I ask, do you think they'll
let me join in maybe?
[Mei] that just means I have an
excuse to snuggle up together.

00:06:38.652 --> 00:06:42.256 position:5% line:83% align:start
[Mei] Oh, good morning, Okazaki!
Now everyone's up.

00:06:42.358 --> 00:06:44.693 position:5% line:89% align:start
Morning, Okazaki. (yawns)

00:06:44.793 --> 00:06:46.895 position:5% line:83% align:start
Morning, you two!
Didn't get much sleep?

00:06:46.997 --> 00:06:49.866 position:5% line:83% align:start
Not really, since we were up
all night talking in bed.

00:06:49.967 --> 00:06:52.471 position:5% line:83% align:start
You were the big topic
of discussion, by the way.

00:06:52.570 --> 00:06:54.172 position:5% line:89% align:start
[TOMOYA] <i>Am I that interesting?</i>

00:06:54.272 --> 00:06:57.310 position:5% line:77% align:start
Hey, Nagisa, why don't you
go back to sleep for
a little while?

00:06:57.410 --> 00:06:59.712 position:5% line:83% align:start
Nah, I'll be fine
once I get going.

00:06:59.812 --> 00:07:03.018 position:5% line:83% align:start
Besides, my classes are over,
so I'm off from school.

00:07:03.118 --> 00:07:05.887 position:5% line:83% align:start
So, you're on vacation and
you spend it working?

00:07:05.987 --> 00:07:07.757 position:5% line:83% align:start
You don't have to
put it that way.

00:07:07.857 --> 00:07:10.694 position:5% line:83% align:start
I just wanted to let Mom and Dad
take some time off for a change.

00:07:10.794 --> 00:07:14.665 position:5% line:83% align:start
I don't think of it as work.
I'm happy to help!

00:07:14.766 --> 00:07:17.136 position:5% line:83% align:start
I know this probably isn't your
idea of a vacation,

00:07:17.236 --> 00:07:20.774 position:5% line:83% align:start
but maybe we can do something
tomorrow instead.

00:07:20.874 --> 00:07:21.908 position:5% line:89% align:start
(ungh)

00:07:22.008 --> 00:07:24.446 position:5% line:83% align:start
Just think of this as
a way to pay your rent.

00:07:24.545 --> 00:07:26.148 position:5% line:89% align:start
Yeah? And what are you gonna do?

00:07:26.248 --> 00:07:30.186 position:5% line:77% align:start
My lovely daughter was kind
enough to give me this time off,
so...

00:07:30.286 --> 00:07:32.756 position:5% line:89% align:start
I'M GONNA PLAY!!

00:07:32.856 --> 00:07:34.526 position:5% line:89% align:start
So long. (maniacal laughter)

00:07:34.625 --> 00:07:38.230 position:5% line:77% align:start
Isn't it wonderful that he's
still a child at heart
after all these years?

00:07:38.330 --> 00:07:39.532 position:5% line:89% align:start
(giggles)

00:07:39.632 --> 00:07:40.766 position:5% line:89% align:start
Sorry to keep you waiting.

00:07:40.866 --> 00:07:43.103 position:5% line:89% align:start
I was busy baking these.

00:07:43.203 --> 00:07:46.508 position:5% line:83% align:start
Wow, that must be your
special recipe, huh?

00:07:46.607 --> 00:07:49.945 position:5% line:83% align:start
Yes! If you'd like to try some,
help yourself.

00:07:50.045 --> 00:07:51.948 position:5% line:89% align:start
[Mei] Yay!

00:07:53.316 --> 00:07:56.421 position:5% line:89% align:start
Ah... (grinding chomp)

00:07:56.521 --> 00:07:57.788 position:5% line:89% align:start
How do you like it?

00:07:57.888 --> 00:07:59.458 position:5% line:83% align:start
[Mei] It's cute!
I realy like the rainbow colors.

00:07:59.559 --> 00:08:01.527 position:5% line:89% align:start
I'm happy to hear it.

00:08:01.626 --> 00:08:04.164 position:5% line:71% align:start
[Tomoya]
"Cute," she says. Very clever.
[Sanae] Still, I wonder if we'll
sell out today?

00:08:04.264 --> 00:08:07.202 position:5% line:77% align:start
[Nagisa]
I'll have to use that next time.
[Mei] Oh, I'm sure we will.

00:08:07.302 --> 00:08:08.602 position:5% line:89% align:start
Sorry to leave so soon,

00:08:08.703 --> 00:08:10.506 position:5% line:83% align:start
but I have a neighborhood
board meeting to attend.

00:08:10.605 --> 00:08:12.908 position:5% line:83% align:start
The shop's in your hands,
so good luck.

00:08:13.008 --> 00:08:15.612 position:5% line:83% align:start
See you later, Mom.
(Mei giggles)

00:08:16.880 --> 00:08:18.816 position:5% line:83% align:start
[LOUDSPEAKER] Please listen to
the following announcement.

00:08:18.916 --> 00:08:23.323 position:5% line:77% align:start
Today, we are collecting
electroinc recyclables from all
houses in this neighborhood.

00:08:23.423 --> 00:08:25.792 position:5% line:83% align:start
If you have any such items that
you are not using,

00:08:25.892 --> 00:08:28.597 position:5% line:83% align:start
such as television sets,
refrigerators, computers...

00:08:28.696 --> 00:08:30.265 position:5% line:89% align:start
Sure is slow.

00:08:30.365 --> 00:08:33.802 position:5% line:77% align:start
You guys had a lot more
customers the last time
I came to visit.

00:08:33.903 --> 00:08:36.105 position:5% line:83% align:start
A lot of students come here for
lunch during the school year,

00:08:36.206 --> 00:08:38.675 position:5% line:83% align:start
but things slow down
on summer break.

00:08:38.775 --> 00:08:40.178 position:5% line:89% align:start
(door opens)

00:08:40.278 --> 00:08:41.246 position:5% line:89% align:start
Ah, hello...

00:08:41.346 --> 00:08:43.648 position:5% line:83% align:start
Hi, welcome to the store.
Here, take one!

00:08:43.748 --> 00:08:44.850 position:5% line:89% align:start
[Tomoya] <i>Damn, she's fast.</i>

00:08:44.950 --> 00:08:46.785 position:5% line:83% align:start
[WOMAN]
Thank you. Oh, look at that.

00:08:46.887 --> 00:08:49.190 position:5% line:83% align:start
Such cute girls are
watching the shop today.

00:08:49.290 --> 00:08:52.194 position:5% line:83% align:start
[Mei] I know!
Nagisa's adorable, isn't she?

00:08:52.294 --> 00:08:54.531 position:5% line:83% align:start
Actually, I think she's
talking about you.

00:08:54.631 --> 00:08:57.167 position:5% line:83% align:start
Oh, no.
I think both of you are cute.

00:08:57.267 --> 00:09:00.871 position:5% line:83% align:start
(giggle) Thank you!
That's nice of you to say.

00:09:00.971 --> 00:09:04.109 position:5% line:89% align:start
Thank you, please come again!

00:09:04.209 --> 00:09:05.877 position:5% line:83% align:start
You weren't helpful at all,
Okazaki.

00:09:05.978 --> 00:09:07.847 position:5% line:83% align:start
You need to step up
your game plan.

00:09:07.947 --> 00:09:10.050 position:5% line:83% align:start
It would have been overkill
with all three of us.

00:09:10.150 --> 00:09:12.487 position:5% line:83% align:start
Any way you look at it,
I'm the third wheel.

00:09:12.587 --> 00:09:14.856 position:5% line:83% align:start
That's not true at all!
Don't say that!

00:09:14.956 --> 00:09:16.091 position:5% line:89% align:start
Even if you're not much help,

00:09:16.192 --> 00:09:19.529 position:5% line:83% align:start
I'm still happy to be
working with you.

00:09:19.629 --> 00:09:20.697 position:5% line:89% align:start
[Mei] Don't worry, Okazaki.

00:09:20.797 --> 00:09:22.066 position:5% line:83% align:start
You just take care
of the register

00:09:22.166 --> 00:09:25.070 position:5% line:83% align:start
while I go outside and
find some new customers.

00:09:25.170 --> 00:09:26.071 position:5% line:89% align:start
Find customers?!

00:09:26.171 --> 00:09:27.072 position:5% line:89% align:start
Wait, Mei!

00:09:27.172 --> 00:09:29.909 position:5% line:83% align:start
[Mei & Tomoya]
Welcome to the store!

00:09:30.009 --> 00:09:34.048 position:5% line:83% align:start
Oh my, that's odd. Akio and
Sanae aren't here today?

00:09:34.148 --> 00:09:36.985 position:5% line:77% align:start
No, we're watching over
the shop for today.
(door opens)

